choices.text:
my relationship with my father. As I age into my mid-20s I'm worried my relationship with him is only going to get more difficult (practical problems will arise that I'm sure he'll want to have oversight over, and will conflate them with his personal idea of what I should be doing) and it's causing me a lot of anxiety. I have OCD, GAD, and depression, and breakthrough anxiety also plays into my relationship with him. I don't want to always be dependent on him, yet I'm dependent on him anyway. He won't hear any kind of me making myself ready for independence. He made over $100,000 last year, I think, and wants to be spending that money on me (bribing me).

My mom wasn't in the picture until I was 8 and only then because my dad remarried her. I even got married when she wasn't in the country, to spite him. My relationship with her is good. We talk about small things sometimes and we don't have any drama or anything, but she doesn't really notice anything big. There was one that happened at the start of 2015 and is kind of hard to explain without it being 2,000 words, but she noticed nothing of the intensity that was going on between me and him at the time.

 

I belong to an ethnic minority, an Eastern 1.5 generation immigrant. I'm, at least semi-educated in my culture.
